id: pm-is1a
title: "As an organization with many repos and thousands of agents, I can federate multiple pm workspaces: cross-workspace context, dependencies, and aggregation"
description: "Explore multi-workspace federation for organizations with many repositories and agent fleets: cross-workspace context, dependencies, aggregation, identity, and governance without weakening single-workspace guarantees."
type: Story
status: open
priority: 4
tags[3]: architecture,"area:storage",long-term
created_at: "2026-07-06T22:00:10.231Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T18:26:39.242Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "Exploration outcome is an ADR under pm-m2u1 covering: monorepo multi-tracker layout (several .agents/pm roots), cross-workspace item references/dependencies, org-level read aggregation (context/list/search across workspaces), and identity/claim semantics across workspaces; explicitly decides what is out of scope; follow-up implementation items filed only after the ADR is accepted"
